post_text:
Hello Everyone

Next week was supposed to be our Homegoing week. Student Council would like to have some virtual fun and have our dress up days anyway. We invited the 6th graders so they can start in on the Homegoing and Homecoming competition!

Here are our days:

Monday: 'Merica-no school this day but it honors Memorial Day
Tuesday: Beach day
Wed: Sports day
Thur: Out and About in Nature
Fri: Spirit Day

This is a pre-homecoming competition, submit a picture of your outfit by noon each day to Mrs. Spencer (espencer@lewalt.k12.mn.us). Mrs. Spencer will then send out a form link at 3:00 for everyone to vote on their favorite picture voting ends at 11:00 am the next day. Winner receives their choice of prizes including activities passes, tshirts, ala cart gift cards, and many others in the fall. The grade with the most overall wins will receive 5 homecoming points toward winning homecoming and owning the spirit stick next year. I know seniors the prizes don't really do much for you, but we would love to see you dress up anyway!

-Mrs. Spencer and the StuCo gang

post_text: Since school closure began, Lewiston-Altura Public Schools have actually been going through about double the milk that we would serve on a typical school day. Students receive milk with breakfast and lunch. We are very proud of this fact in the face of the milk dumping news in our area, and would be happy to see those numbers grow with even more students coming to pickup meals from 7-8:30 or 4-5:30 daily at our three pickup sites. We are proud of our farming community and want to provide all the help that we can. Meals have also included yogurt and cheese. Our vendors purchase from farm to school producers which helps our local economy. Help our local farmers by stopping to get the two free meals a day for all family members 18 and under. We should be serving well over 800 students a day, providing 1600 meals. We are at about 75% of this goal.

In an effort to address the growing issue of vaping, the Winona County Alliance for Substance Abuse Prevention (ASAP) is going to be presenting at the high school open house tomorrow evening, January 28. There will be two 30 minute presentations, the first at 5:30 pm and the second at 6:15 pm. Both presentations will be in the library/media center.

This presentation is geared towards education about the hazards of vaping as well as recognition of the various types of devices. There will also be an opportunity to ask questions that you may have on the subject. Together, we can start this semester off on the right foot!

post_text:
Congratulations Creighton Sauer!!!

Creighton will receive his Swine Proficiency State award on April 29th at the FFA Awards Ceremony at The University of Minnesota. He will also be presented with his Region 8 Star Farmer Award that day. He is currently competing for Minnesota State Star Farmer too and that award will also be presented on the 29th.

He will get his Swine Proficiency Application back after the April 29th award ceremony and have a month to make any final changes to his final application before submitting it to the National competition in June. In mid- August he will receive word on his National placing. If he is in the top 4 in the country he will be asked to attend The FFA National Convention in Indianapolis, IN from October 30th-Nov. 2nd
text:
Congratulations Creighton Sauer!!!

post_text: Lewiston-Altura School District is proud to announce Maddy Neldner as our local female Triple ‘A’ Award representative. The Triple ‘A’ Award is a recognition program for high school seniors who excel in Academics, Arts and Athletics. The Minnesota State High School League has sponsored the award since 1988. Award representatives are selected through a multi-level process. Each high school selects one male and one female as their local representatives. Those representatives are then sent on to the regional level to compete against other regional school representatives. From that pool of candidates, the region will select one male and one female candidate that will be sent on to the state level. Congratulations, Maddy, and good luck at the regional level!
